MONGO DB
mongosh - start the mongo server shell
db -display the current db
use students - switch to or create a new database students
show dbs - display current databases

CREATE DATABASE AND COLLECTION IN DATABASE
use myNewDatabase
db.myCollection.insertOne( { x: 1 } );  if collection does not exist it is created.

FILTERING
kubu> db.test.find({'name':'mark'}, projection={'_id':false, 'name':true, 'marks':true, })
[ { name: 'mark', marks: [ 23, 45 ] } ]
kubu> db.test.find({'name':'mark'}, projection={'_id':false, 'name':false })
[ { marks: [ 23, 45 ], subjects: [ 'eng', 'sci' ] } ]
db.test.find({'name':{'$in':['mark','agnes']}}) sql equivalent select from test where name in ('mark','agnes')
mongodb operators $in, $lt, $gt, $eq, $regex
The logical AND is implicit for query across two fields
db.test.find({'name':'mark', 'subjects':'eng'})
cursor = db.test.find({"$or": [{"name": "agnes"}, {"subjects": 'eng'}]})

