pandas dataframe is dict object with keys as columns and key values as columns values. dataframe is also a list of records(list, tuple) as rows
mongo collection-(table-dataframe) is list of dict(documents). each dict is a document(records). this makes it possible for the records to be of variable length each of the dict(document) in the list dont need to have the same number of keys

example of list of dict(document) making documents and table
[{'name':'george', 'class':5, 'parent':'rosemary'} ,
            {'name':'rita', 'class':7, 'parent':'rosemary'},
            {'name':'james', 'class':8, 'parent':'karugu'},]
            
